1
00:00:36,110 --> 00:00:41,240
♪In rain or shine♪

2
00:00:41,780 --> 00:00:46,870
♪When you're around,
the sun shines through♪

3
00:00:47,220 --> 00:00:52,640
♪Spare ourselves the endless thoughts
and guessing games♪

4
00:00:52,930 --> 00:00:58,880
♪Let's just meet
and escape these frames♪

5
00:00:59,360 --> 00:01:02,600
♪I stand within the shadows deep♪

6
00:01:02,880 --> 00:01:08,030
♪My hand outstretched,
your rescue I keep♪

7
00:01:08,220 --> 00:01:12,850
♪Even if the world falls apart♪

8
00:01:13,170 --> 00:01:15,870
♪No distance is too far♪

9
00:01:17,260 --> 00:01:21,390
♪To stop us from coming together♪

10
00:01:21,720 --> 00:01:27,710
♪Through the night,
you're at the end of the line♪

11
00:01:28,710 --> 00:01:32,730
♪To protect you is my humble wish♪

12
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:36,920
♪Farewell, to the timid soul I knew♪

13
00:01:37,270 --> 00:01:42,550
♪It was you who made me brave and new♪

14
00:01:42,550 --> 00:01:46,180
=Always Home=
(Adapted from Xiao Ge's novel, Always Home)

15
00:01:46,260 --> 00:01:49,180
=Episode 30=
(Always Home)

16
00:02:51,420 --> 00:02:52,900
(I dreamed of these woods.)

17
00:02:53,990 --> 00:02:54,740
(In my dreams,)

18
00:02:55,700 --> 00:02:57,230
(I ask these trees over and over again)

19
00:02:57,790 --> 00:02:58,900
(if they've seen my dad.)

20
00:03:00,230 --> 00:03:01,860
(But none of them answered me.)

21
00:03:03,830 --> 00:03:05,390
(If only the trees could talk...)

22
00:03:06,620 --> 00:03:07,790
(Because you're the only ones)

23
00:03:08,070 --> 00:03:09,350
(who saw him for the last time.)

24
00:03:10,900 --> 00:03:11,740
(Now,)

25
00:03:12,510 --> 00:03:13,350
(I realize)

26
00:03:14,550 --> 00:03:16,140
(that perhaps the rustling)

27
00:03:17,300 --> 00:03:19,390
(of every leaf as the wind blows)

28
00:03:20,620 --> 00:03:21,700
(is a goodbye)

29
00:03:21,700 --> 00:03:22,830
(you didn't get to say.)

30
00:03:24,460 --> 00:03:25,550
(They will come together)

31
00:03:25,550 --> 00:03:26,830
(as the gentlest force)

32
00:03:27,955 --> 00:03:30,111
(to keep me from being afraid
of the road ahead,)

33
00:03:31,444 --> 00:03:32,860
(from dwelling on the past.)

34
00:04:11,260 --> 00:04:16,020
(Market Status and Trends
of Second-hand Books)

35
00:04:22,022 --> 00:04:24,030
(Yangwu is
a Secondhand Book Trading Website.)

36
00:04:24,710 --> 00:04:25,300
This concept

37
00:04:25,380 --> 00:04:26,955
was born out of a bookcrossing event

38
00:04:26,955 --> 00:04:27,860
I did in high school.

39
00:04:27,990 --> 00:04:29,380
That long-ago event

40
00:04:30,180 --> 00:04:33,260
proved the simplicity and sincerity

41
00:04:34,150 --> 00:04:35,060
of human feelings.

42
00:04:35,260 --> 00:04:36,710
But when we enter the society,

43
00:04:36,940 --> 00:04:38,590
in this multi-dimensional world

44
00:04:38,740 --> 00:04:40,550
of convenient transport
and communication,

45
00:04:40,910 --> 00:04:42,740
we find that the distance between people

46
00:04:42,844 --> 00:04:44,311
is getting further and further away.

47
00:04:45,300 --> 00:04:46,150
I've always believed

48
00:04:46,150 --> 00:04:47,888
that people are not isolated islands.

49
00:04:48,150 --> 00:04:49,300
We spend our lives

50
00:04:49,350 --> 00:04:50,866
searching for a family to snuggle with,

51
00:04:50,911 --> 00:04:51,910
to warm up to,

52
00:04:52,230 --> 00:04:53,940
as well as companions
to reflect our souls.

53
00:04:54,590 --> 00:04:55,990
They are the stars of the night sky,

54
00:04:56,620 --> 00:04:57,860
(the lighthouse of the sea,)

55
00:04:58,940 --> 00:05:00,420
(and the everlasting sun.)

56
00:05:02,266 --> 00:05:03,910
(They are the proof that we are alive,)

57
00:05:04,740 --> 00:05:06,180
(and the meaning of our existence.)

58
00:05:06,910 --> 00:05:07,740
(It's when we start)

59
00:05:07,740 --> 00:05:09,060
(to burn for each other)

60
00:05:09,620 --> 00:05:11,910
that the world becomes so bright

61
00:05:11,990 --> 00:05:12,820
and colorful.

62
00:05:12,985 --> 00:05:13,710
(Yangwu's Proposal)

63
00:05:13,710 --> 00:05:14,380
Therefore,

64
00:05:14,790 --> 00:05:16,620
a book is not just a book.

65
00:05:16,990 --> 00:05:18,110
It's the port

66
00:05:18,180 --> 00:05:19,820
of communication between people.

67
00:05:20,260 --> 00:05:22,030
It is a shelter for the lonely,

68
00:05:22,150 --> 00:05:23,620
a haven for the wandering,

69
00:05:24,060 --> 00:05:25,820
a home where warm lights

70
00:05:25,990 --> 00:05:26,940
are always on

71
00:05:27,260 --> 00:05:29,888
and the door is open
for the return of the wanderer.

72
00:05:41,380 --> 00:05:41,820
Fu Ying,

73
00:05:42,244 --> 00:05:43,350
I don't need this anymore.

74
00:05:43,350 --> 00:05:43,820
For you.

75
00:05:46,030 --> 00:05:46,910
You...

76
00:05:50,550 --> 00:05:50,990
How is it?

77
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:53,311
Have you got the results
from the meeting?

78
00:05:59,860 --> 00:06:00,500
What

79
00:06:01,150 --> 00:06:02,110
are you doing?

80
00:06:02,820 --> 00:06:03,860
I'm moving

81
00:06:04,300 --> 00:06:05,380
to the 10th floor.

82
00:06:06,260 --> 00:06:07,030
The 10th floor?

83
00:06:08,060 --> 00:06:09,300
So our plan is approved?

84
00:06:10,180 --> 00:06:11,710
To be precise,

85
00:06:12,555 --> 00:06:13,866
she'll go to the 10th floor,

86
00:06:13,933 --> 00:06:15,180
and I'll go to the ground floor.

87
00:06:15,377 --> 00:06:16,888
What are you doing on the ground floor?

88
00:06:17,230 --> 00:06:18,500
Take a cab and go home.

89
00:06:20,150 --> 00:06:20,940
The plan

90
00:06:22,500 --> 00:06:23,420
didn't get approved.

91
00:06:30,620 --> 00:06:32,060
You don't have to blame yourself.

92
00:06:32,555 --> 00:06:33,470
It's not our problem

93
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:34,844
that the plan didn't get approved.

94
00:06:34,940 --> 00:06:35,590
A long time ago,

95
00:06:35,710 --> 00:06:36,860
I wanted to tell you.

96
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:38,350
No matter how well

97
00:06:38,350 --> 00:06:39,180
our plan is done,

98
00:06:39,311 --> 00:06:41,155
it will still be rejected
by the company.

99
00:06:41,420 --> 00:06:42,030
Huandao is a

100
00:06:42,030 --> 00:06:43,060
very mature organization.

101
00:06:43,100 --> 00:06:44,470
Every project that is incorporated

102
00:06:44,500 --> 00:06:45,610
into the company's territory

103
00:06:45,610 --> 00:06:47,259
and every piece of content
that is produced

104
00:06:47,260 --> 00:06:49,355
is closely related to the company's
future development.

105
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:50,500
It's never going to shift

106
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:52,711
at the will of some of us newcomers
to the company.

107
00:06:54,550 --> 00:06:55,860
So,

108
00:06:56,260 --> 00:06:57,260
they've been making us

109
00:06:57,755 --> 00:06:59,180
waste our time from the beginning?

110
00:07:00,620 --> 00:07:01,710
The company already gave us

111
00:07:01,740 --> 00:07:02,790
a one percent chance.

112
00:07:03,533 --> 00:07:05,260
It's just
that we're all ordinary people.

113
00:07:05,860 --> 00:07:06,990
And miracles

114
00:07:07,022 --> 00:07:08,888
don't always happen to ordinary people.

115
00:07:10,550 --> 00:07:11,990
I still don't quite get it.

116
00:07:13,110 --> 00:07:13,620
And you...

117
00:07:13,990 --> 00:07:15,470
Want to ask me why I got to stay?

118
00:07:16,060 --> 00:07:17,060
And got a promotion?

119
00:07:17,910 --> 00:07:19,380
Well, actually, I got an offer letter

120
00:07:19,420 --> 00:07:21,030
from headquarters before you got here.

121
00:07:21,355 --> 00:07:22,600
I was offered the position

122
00:07:22,620 --> 00:07:23,777
of department manager.

123
00:07:26,180 --> 00:07:27,150
So,

124
00:07:27,620 --> 00:07:28,940
Fu Ying, you're the spy.

125
00:07:29,470 --> 00:07:30,711
You're such a good actress.

126
00:07:31,110 --> 00:07:32,420
But I don't understand

127
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:34,740
why you've been working hard

128
00:07:34,740 --> 00:07:35,550
with us for a month,

129
00:07:36,420 --> 00:07:36,860
doing...

130
00:07:36,990 --> 00:07:38,150
Doing this for nothing.

131
00:07:39,790 --> 00:07:40,420
I have no idea.

132
00:07:41,180 --> 00:07:42,820
Maybe I was still harboring illusions.

133
00:07:43,380 --> 00:07:44,300
That we're

134
00:07:44,300 --> 00:07:45,550
the one percent that survived.

135
00:07:46,420 --> 00:07:47,470
It's not for nothing.

136
00:07:48,180 --> 00:07:48,910
I'm just trying

137
00:07:48,910 --> 00:07:50,180
to pull off one last

138
00:07:51,470 --> 00:07:52,710
silly romance

139
00:07:53,060 --> 00:07:54,230
with my companions.

140
00:08:04,230 --> 00:08:04,740
Fu Ying,

141
00:08:08,380 --> 00:08:08,820
thank you.

142
00:08:18,910 --> 00:08:19,500
What about you?

143
00:08:20,710 --> 00:08:21,590
Do you want

144
00:08:21,910 --> 00:08:23,150
to fight to stay again?

145
00:08:24,030 --> 00:08:25,790
Xichi, I'm sorry.

146
00:08:27,022 --> 00:08:28,500
It's impossible for me to stay.

147
00:08:30,420 --> 00:08:31,180
Why?

148
00:08:33,310 --> 00:08:34,070
To sum up,

149
00:08:34,230 --> 00:08:35,070
in the future, Yangwu

150
00:08:35,070 --> 00:08:35,900
will not only be able

151
00:08:35,955 --> 00:08:37,239
to trade second-hand books,

152
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,860
but will also be able
to build a community

153
00:08:38,866 --> 00:08:39,822
based on interests

154
00:08:39,900 --> 00:08:40,620
and meet more

155
00:08:40,740 --> 00:08:41,780
like-minded people.

156
00:08:42,190 --> 00:08:43,350
After all this time,

157
00:08:43,740 --> 00:08:44,430
this is what

158
00:08:44,430 --> 00:08:45,260
you've come up with?

159
00:08:45,990 --> 00:08:48,190
Huandao is not a charity organization.

160
00:08:48,350 --> 00:08:49,710
According to your plan,

161
00:08:49,830 --> 00:08:50,620
we need to invest

162
00:08:50,740 --> 00:08:51,710
a lot of time

163
00:08:51,830 --> 00:08:53,555
and manpower to manage the website.

164
00:08:53,710 --> 00:08:55,900
If the cost-effectiveness
of the website is so low,

165
00:08:56,260 --> 00:08:57,500
what is the use of keeping it?

166
00:08:57,990 --> 00:08:58,740
Young man,

167
00:08:59,230 --> 00:09:00,990
having an idea and trying it out

168
00:09:01,070 --> 00:09:02,140
is a good thing.

169
00:09:02,860 --> 00:09:03,500
How about this?

170
00:09:03,620 --> 00:09:04,990
I'm giving you one more chance.

171
00:09:05,022 --> 00:09:06,230
You can follow the original...

172
00:09:06,230 --> 00:09:06,860
No need.

173
00:09:09,020 --> 00:09:09,710
What did you say?

174
00:09:14,380 --> 00:09:15,110
I said,

175
00:09:15,990 --> 00:09:16,780
I don't need it.

176
00:09:17,710 --> 00:09:18,540
I'm quitting.

177
00:09:19,230 --> 00:09:20,740
You're all about money.

178
00:09:21,110 --> 00:09:22,020
Doctor?

179
00:09:23,230 --> 00:09:23,900
Engineer?

180
00:09:23,990 --> 00:09:25,190
Technician?

181
00:09:25,444 --> 00:09:27,466
To put it bluntly,
you're just a capitalist.

182
00:09:28,430 --> 00:09:30,380
You are a wolf in sheep's clothing.

183
00:09:30,740 --> 00:09:31,260
Zhou Ye,

184
00:09:31,311 --> 00:09:32,844
do you know what you're talking about?

185
00:09:33,070 --> 00:09:33,830
Young man,

186
00:09:34,140 --> 00:09:35,780
I'd advise you to hold back your temper.

187
00:09:36,190 --> 00:09:37,620
Don't think too highly of yourself.

188
00:09:38,540 --> 00:09:39,540
You're just nothing.

189
00:09:43,140 --> 00:09:45,190
Calm down.

190
00:09:51,830 --> 00:09:52,350
I...

191
00:09:54,780 --> 00:09:55,350
Let go!

192
00:09:57,140 --> 00:09:57,540
You...

193
00:09:57,830 --> 00:09:58,430
Go away!

194
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:00,070
I'll beat you to death!

195
00:10:01,350 --> 00:10:02,140
Come back here!

196
00:10:04,620 --> 00:10:05,780
Starting today,

197
00:10:06,470 --> 00:10:09,140
I am the first person
to straighten out the workplace.

198
00:10:09,860 --> 00:10:10,710
I'm the man

199
00:10:11,020 --> 00:10:12,830
Huandao can never have.

200
00:10:13,333 --> 00:10:14,222
Do I stand by you?

201
00:10:14,900 --> 00:10:16,070
Bring me the box.

202
00:10:16,230 --> 00:10:16,830
This one?

203
00:10:18,444 --> 00:10:19,733
What do you need this for?

204
00:10:20,710 --> 00:10:21,990
I'm leaving with you.

205
00:10:24,310 --> 00:10:25,110
Actually, the boss

206
00:10:25,155 --> 00:10:27,022
doesn't necessarily want you to leave.

207
00:10:29,310 --> 00:10:30,710
It's me who can't stay any longer.

208
00:10:31,860 --> 00:10:33,430
After all, it's just that Huandao and I

209
00:10:33,430 --> 00:10:34,822
don't share the same philosophy.

210
00:10:41,555 --> 00:10:43,244
Then I wish you both the best of luck

211
00:10:43,244 --> 00:10:44,555
in finding your own paths.

212
00:10:44,830 --> 00:10:45,620
Thank you, Fu Ying.

213
00:10:47,070 --> 00:10:47,780
Fu Ying,

214
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:49,711
take good care of yourself.

215
00:10:57,070 --> 00:10:57,860
Pack up.

216
00:10:59,710 --> 00:11:00,380
The following

217
00:11:00,500 --> 00:11:02,244
are some of the data produced
by our team.

218
00:11:02,780 --> 00:11:03,990
The treated cells

219
00:11:04,230 --> 00:11:05,310
were stained

220
00:11:05,540 --> 00:11:06,830
and the percentage of apoptosis

221
00:11:06,950 --> 00:11:08,710
was detected by flow cytometry.

222
00:11:09,020 --> 00:11:09,540
Among them,

223
00:11:09,830 --> 00:11:10,380
A and B

224
00:11:10,590 --> 00:11:12,110
represent the reference

225
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:13,950
of control group and treated group...

226
00:11:13,955 --> 00:11:15,666
Is there anything wrong with these data?

227
00:11:16,230 --> 00:11:16,740
No.

228
00:11:17,070 --> 00:11:17,990
I did it all by myself.

229
00:11:18,140 --> 00:11:19,020
Nothing can go wrong.

230
00:11:19,430 --> 00:11:20,500
Look at it carefully.

231
00:11:20,711 --> 00:11:21,990
Are you sure nothing's wrong?

232
00:11:27,088 --> 00:11:27,830
Senior Gao...

233
00:11:27,830 --> 00:11:28,540
What's the matter?

234
00:11:28,900 --> 00:11:29,590
Chen Huan'er,

235
00:11:30,190 --> 00:11:31,110
what's going wrong?

236
00:11:33,470 --> 00:11:35,620
The data should be the old version.

237
00:11:36,310 --> 00:11:37,900
He must have opened the wrong file.

238
00:11:38,740 --> 00:11:40,230
Even if you opened the wrong one,

239
00:11:40,933 --> 00:11:42,860
can't you tell
if your own experimental data

240
00:11:42,900 --> 00:11:44,190
is correct or not?

241
00:11:45,140 --> 00:11:45,830
Tell me.

242
00:11:46,110 --> 00:11:46,780
How much

243
00:11:47,190 --> 00:11:48,710
did you participate in this experiment?

244
00:11:49,430 --> 00:11:49,780
I...

245
00:11:49,950 --> 00:11:50,230
Well...

246
00:11:50,620 --> 00:11:51,230
Chen Huan'er,

247
00:11:51,540 --> 00:11:52,230
tell me.

248
00:11:57,740 --> 00:11:58,380
Professor Qiu,

249
00:11:59,266 --> 00:12:00,511
the data was prepared

250
00:12:00,533 --> 00:12:01,777
by me and Tian Chi.

251
00:12:02,620 --> 00:12:03,710
Senior Gao Ang

252
00:12:06,430 --> 00:12:07,620
usually just gives guidance.

253
00:12:08,620 --> 00:12:10,470
You can't even understand

254
00:12:10,500 --> 00:12:11,260
the basics,

255
00:12:11,380 --> 00:12:12,470
so how can you mentor

256
00:12:12,500 --> 00:12:13,430
your juniors?

257
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:15,140
Get down.

258
00:12:15,563 --> 00:12:16,860
Chen Huan'er, present it.

259
00:12:18,140 --> 00:12:18,830
Yes.

260
00:12:26,260 --> 00:12:26,900
I'm sorry.

261
00:12:27,020 --> 00:12:28,070
Let me correct

262
00:12:28,110 --> 00:12:29,355
our experimental data for you.

263
00:12:31,470 --> 00:12:32,260
You have no idea

264
00:12:32,260 --> 00:12:33,740
how embarrassing it was today.

265
00:12:33,990 --> 00:12:35,470
So many people were in the hall.

266
00:12:36,990 --> 00:12:37,470
Anyway,

267
00:12:38,430 --> 00:12:39,380
Gao Ang

268
00:12:39,380 --> 00:12:40,990
got what he deserved.

269
00:12:41,540 --> 00:12:42,110
That's good.

270
00:12:42,177 --> 00:12:43,950
I don't need to teach him
a lesson for you?

271
00:12:44,950 --> 00:12:46,430
Don't bother

272
00:12:46,470 --> 00:12:47,500
to do that for me.

273
00:12:47,620 --> 00:12:48,780
I can still handle it.

274
00:12:50,110 --> 00:12:51,590
I'm going to have a feast today.

275
00:12:51,620 --> 00:12:52,710
I'm going to treat myself.

276
00:12:53,830 --> 00:12:55,190
Can you add a pair of chopsticks?

277
00:12:55,288 --> 00:12:56,577
Add a pair of chopsticks?

278
00:12:57,710 --> 00:12:58,590
What do you mean?

279
00:12:58,800 --> 00:12:59,733
Look to the right.

280
00:13:09,470 --> 00:13:10,540
Piggy Jing!

281
00:13:15,230 --> 00:13:16,590
Why are you here?

282
00:13:16,780 --> 00:13:17,380
Zhou Ye and I

283
00:13:17,380 --> 00:13:18,830
left Huandao together.

284
00:13:19,190 --> 00:13:19,780
From now on, we

285
00:13:19,866 --> 00:13:21,444
won't need to be separated anymore.

286
00:13:21,540 --> 00:13:22,780
What do you mean?

287
00:13:23,430 --> 00:13:24,540
That means

288
00:13:25,140 --> 00:13:26,110
I'm now

289
00:13:26,140 --> 00:13:27,070
unemployed.

290
